Hi! My name is Deziree for long, but dez/i for short. This is my dog Vida. Without assigning anyone blame, growing up left a mark or two on me. But this sweet, lil bug eyed, loud, shaking creature was with me through a lot of it. Weird to say that just her being there really helped me. She’s my buddy—indescribable if you never had a close bond with an animal. 

She’s not dead. I thought I’d share what I care about every now and again so there’s maybe a glimpse of who I am as a person. After all, y’all are mostly just seeing art I do. And although you can interpret that in so many ways and maybe come up with some sort of idea of me, idk how accurate it’ll be! 

So, here’s something a little more sentimental than usual. Vida Rey—one of two dogs I grew up with who changed my life in what’s probably an overtly dramatic way to some :,)

AHHHH! It’s a screeching, yelling lamb! Thank you, Cy, for the continued support!! 

Also, I’ll be taking walk-ins with my mentor @botanicalsabbath today till 4:30! First come, first serve. List will be out at 10:30am 🥰
